<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Jubal on 05-25-2001 05:19 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">I agree with the original post, and consider myself fortunate that I was 52ish when celestial heal came out. It seems to be such a great spell that many clerics become overly dependent on it. It's a perfect downtime heal for casters and hybrids, but when someone is being actively beat on it needs the support of a direct heal.

I'd suggest for clerics who view it as their primary heal to play for a week without memming it to hone their direct-healing skills, it'll be worth it in the end.

As far as the pre-engagement use of celestials, I am definitely all for that. I see a multi-pull of planar+ mobs come in and the first thing I do is pop a CE on the enchanter and sometimes the shaman as well. To use a celestial in this way, your spell must hit your target before the mobs start beating on him.

</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
